it.uniroma3.mat.extendedset
Interface ExtendedSet<T>

Type Parameters:
T - the type of elements maintained by this set
All Superinterfaces:
java.lang.Cloneable, java.util.Collection<T>, java.lang.Comparable<ExtendedSet<T>>, java.lang.Iterable<T>, java.util.Set<T>, java.util.SortedSet<T>
All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractExtendedSet, ConciseSet, FastSet, IndexedSet, MatrixSet
public interface ExtendedSet<T>
extends java.util.SortedSet<T>, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable<ExtendedSet<T>>

A SortedSet with fast intersection/union/difference and other set operations.

It collects all the basic functionalities and the interface of AbstractExtendedSet, ConciseSet, FastSet, and IndexedSet. AbstractExtendedSet is a base abstract class for all other classes.

NOTE FOR PACKAGE DEVELOPERS: Every modification to this class must be reflected in those inner classes implementing the ExtendedSet.Unmodifiable interface within ConciseSet, FastSet, and IndexedSet (not in MatrixSet). Obviously, all classes AbstractExtendedSet, ConciseSet, FastSet, IndexedSet, and MatrixSet must be checked in order to decide whether the modification impacts AbstractExtendedSet only or the other ones.

powerSet

java.util.List<? extends ExtendedSet<T>> powerSet()
Computes the power-set of the current set.

It is a particular implementation of the algorithm Apriori. The power-set does not contains the empty set. The list is sorted according to the lexicographical order provided by the sorted set.

Returns:
the power-set

powerSet

java.util.List<? extends ExtendedSet<T>> powerSet(int min,
                                                  int max)
Computes a subset of the power-set of the current set, composed by those subsets that have cardinality between min and max.

It is a particular implementation of the algorithm Apriori. The power-set does not contains the empty set. The list is sorted according to the lexicographical order provided by the sorted set.

Parameters:
min - minimum subset size (greater than zero)
max - maximum subset size
Returns:
the power-set
